headlines.description: — Kevin Durant feels a sense of comfort.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 23 points in Charlotte in Suns debut

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 41 points and the Detroit Pistons called one too many timeouts, helping the Chicago Bulls hold on for a 117-115 win Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 41, Bulls top Pistons 117-115 after TO blunder

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum is two days shy of his 25th birthday and has already accomplished more than many of his peers will in their entire careers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 41 to help Celtics outlast Cavaliers 117-113

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid got the night off. The Philadelphia 76ers didn't need him anyway.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey scores 27, 76ers roll past Heat 119-96 without Embiid

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Whatever Jalen Brunson and Tom Thibodeau were discussing before bumping fists near the end of the game, it wasn't the point guard's brilliant play.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 39, Knicks rout Nets 142-118 for 7th straight

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 30 points, Ja Morant added 20 and the Memphis Grizzlies breezed by Houston 113-99 on Wednesday night to send the Rockets to their 11th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane scores 30 points to lead Grizzlies over Rockets 113-99

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo wants to make sure the Milwaukee Bucks shouldn't rely too much on the 3-point shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks rout Magic 139-117, extend winning streak to 16 games

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder scored 22 of his 26 points in the second half and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 123-117 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dennis Schroder scores 26 points, Lakers top Thunder 123-117

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram stole the spotlight from the anticipated reunion between Damian Lillard and CJ McCollum.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram has 40 points, Pelicans beat Trail Blazers 121-110
